name: Heat
summary: The Miami Heat advanced to face the Celtics in the NBA playoffs after defeating the Bulls. The Heat's victory coincides with a CDC report highlighting the record-high health emergencies caused by heat in the US last year. Scientific American emphasizes the role of climate change in recent heat waves, including a deadly one in West Africa. An NBA.com article provides details on the upcoming Celtics-Heat playoff series. Reuters warns of future extreme heat events in West Africa due to climate change. CNET explores the cost-saving potential of heat pumps for Americans. The Miami Herald discusses the Heat's draft prospects and Adebayo's Defensive Player of the Year nomination. Amidst this, Florida has banned local heat regulations for outdoor workers, drawing criticism from experts. Additionally, Bloomberg Law reports on the debate surrounding worker heat safety laws, which are facing preemption efforts in red states.

summary: This year's Passover celebration is marked by a somber mood as the ongoing conflict in Gaza weighs heavily on Jewish communities. Amidst heightened tensions, there are concerns about the ability of Jews to come together and fully embrace the holiday's themes of freedom and liberation. However, commentators also emphasize the importance of continuing to mark Passover as a reminder of the resilience and hope that have sustained the Jewish people throughout history. Despite the challenging circumstances, the holiday serves as an opportunity to reflect on the pursuit of a better world and to find solace in the shared experiences and ancient traditions that bind Jews together.
